#let 中文摘要 = [
  针对高校电子实验中“原理图正确但实物接错”难以发现、师生比偏高、教学诊断需可解释且安全的痛点，本文提出 LabGuardian——一个运行于英特尔边缘平台的神经—符号解耦电路实验诊断系统。系统以多视角图像为输入，经关键点检测与孔位吸附重构面包板的引脚级电气网表；由确定性图比对算法承担对错判断、输出可审计的结构化错误事实，再由智能体在受约束的证据范围内生成自然语言解释，并以不可绕过的确定性校验器拦截无依据陈述，从根本上抑制大模型幻觉。教学解释模型经双教师蒸馏与 INT4 量化后部署于 Intel DK-2500，借助 NPU、iGPU 与 CPU 的异构分工实现低功耗本地推理。实验表明，检索契约的引入使端侧小模型在不更换模型的前提下显著提升诊断接地能力，系统可在 8GB 内存边缘设备上以约 10 瓦完成端到端诊断与解释。
]
#let 中文关键词 = ("面包板电路诊断", "神经—符号", "边缘智能", "知识蒸馏", "可解释人工智能")

#let 英文摘要 = [
  To address the difficulty of detecting "schematic-correct but wrongly-wired" breadboard circuits, the high student-to-teacher ratio, and the demand for explainable and safe diagnosis in undergraduate electronics laboratories, this paper presents LabGuardian, a neuro-symbolic circuit-diagnosis system running on an Intel edge platform. Taking multi-view images as input, the system reconstructs a pin-level electrical netlist through keypoint detection and hole snapping; a deterministic graph-comparison algorithm makes the correct/incorrect judgement and emits auditable structured error facts, after which an agent generates natural-language explanations strictly within the retrieved evidence, while an unbypassable deterministic verifier rejects any ungrounded statement so as to fundamentally suppress hallucination. The teaching-explanation model, obtained by dual-teacher distillation and INT4 quantization, is deployed on the Intel DK-2500 and performs low-power local inference through heterogeneous NPU/iGPU/CPU scheduling. Experiments show that introducing the retrieval contract substantially improves the diagnostic grounding of the on-device small model without changing the model itself, and that the system completes end-to-end diagnosis and explanation at about 10 W on an 8 GB edge device.
]
#let 英文关键词 = ("breadboard circuit diagnosis", "neuro-symbolic", "edge intelligence", "knowledge distillation", "explainable AI")


